{r}‚ÜêOpenGitShell y;bool;cmd;home;path;pathToGitExe;paths;space
‚çù Opens a Terminal in `y`.\\
‚çù `y` must be one of:\\
‚çù   * Fully qualified path to a Git-managed project
‚çù   * Fully qualified name of a namespace that is an opened Cider project\\
‚çù   * A dot (`.`) for "current directory"
‚çù Returns always 0\\
‚çù This has been tested on Windows, Mac OS and Ubuntu.
 r‚Üê0
 :If (,'.')‚â°,y
     path‚Üê'.'
     space‚Üê''
 :Else
     (space path)‚ÜêEstablishProject y
 :EndIf
 :Select ‚éïC A.GetOperatingSystem ‚ç¨
 :Case 'win'
     paths‚Üê';'A.Split 2 ‚éïNQ #'GetEnvironment' 'PATH'
     :If 1=+/bool‚Üê‚à®/¬®'\git\bin'‚àò‚ç∑¬®‚éïC paths
         home‚Üê(bool‚ç≥1)‚äÉpaths
         pathToGitExe‚Üêhome,'\sh.exe'
     :Else
         home‚Üê(‚ä¢2 ‚éïNQ #'GetEnvironment' 'ProgramFiles'),'/Git/bin'
         pathToGitExe‚Üêhome,'/sh.exe'
         :If ~‚éïNEXISTS home
             'GitBash not found!'‚éïSIGNAL 6
         :EndIf
     :EndIf
     cmd‚Üê('"',pathToGitExe,'" --cd="',((-(¬Ø1‚Üëpath)‚àä'/\')‚Üìpath),'"')
     ‚éïSH cmd''
 :Case 'lin'
     cmd‚Üê'gnome-terminal -- $SHELL -c "cd ',((-(¬Ø1‚Üëpath)‚àä'/\')‚Üìpath),';git status; exec $SHELL"'
     ‚éïSH cmd
 :Case 'mac'
     cmd‚Üê'osascript -e ''tell app "terminal" to do script "cd ',((-(¬Ø1‚Üëpath)‚àä'/\')‚Üìpath),';git status "'''
     ‚éïSH cmd
 :EndSelect
‚çùDone
